obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (68679)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title Incorporation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68679&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby enacted, that the persons whose names appear in the Schedule`
  line `No. 1, hereunto annexed, shall, from the 14th day of March, 1838, form a corporate body for the`
  line `Warehousing of Goods, either in bond or otherwise, by the name of the Bengal Bonded Warehouse`
  line Association
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (68680)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Power to sue and be sued, and to acquire, hold and transfer property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68680&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1 * * * The said`
  line `Association shall sue and be sued by its corporate name, and shall use such common seal as the`
  line `Directors of the said Association shall from time to time appoint, and may acquire, may hold`
  line `absolutely, may hold by way of pledge, and may transfer, any description of property whatever`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (68681)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Capital Stock and shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68681&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * The sum of Rs. 10,00,000 subscribed for the purpose of the`
  line `said Association by the persons hereby incorporated, shall be the Capital Stock of the said`
  line `Association, and shall be divided into 2,000 shares of 500 Rupees each, and ^2* * * every one of the`
  line `persons hereby incorporated shall have one share of such Capital Stock for every 500 Rupees which`
  line `such person shall have subscribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word “that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891 s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (68682)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Registering of names of proprietors. Register to be open to inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68682&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1 * * * The Directors of the said Association shall`
  line `cause the names, additions, and places of residence of the proprietors of shares in the said Capital`
  line `Stock, and the number of shares held by each proprietor, to be registered in a book, and the said`
  line `shares shall in such book be numbered, beginning from No. 1, and such book shall be kept at the`
  line `office of the said Association,`
  line
  line `Register to be open to inspection.--and shall there be open to the inspection of all persons`
  line `during the usual hours of business.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (68683)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Share-certificates.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68683&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1 * * * A certificate signed by three Directors of the said Association shall`
  line `be delivered to every proprietor of the said Capital Stock, and ^2* * * it shall be at the option of every`
  line `proprietor of several shares to receive one certificate for all the shares of such proprietor, or one`
  line `certificate for each of those shares or several certificates, each of which may be for any number of`
  line `those shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word “that” omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (68684)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Transfer of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68684&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1 * * * Any share or shares of the said Capital Stock may be transferred`
  line `by indorsement made on the certificate for such share or shares by the proprietor of such share or`
  line `shares, or by the Attorney of such proprietor duly authorized thereunto; provided always, that such`
  line `indorsement shall specify the name of the party to whom the transfer is made; and provided also that`
  line `no such indorsement shall be effectual to transfer any such share or shares until such indorsement`
  line `shall have been registered in a Register to be kept for that purpose at the office of the said`
  line `Association, and until a note of such registration, and of the date thereof, shall have been made on the`
  line `back of the indorsed certificate under the hand of an officer appointed for that purpose by the`
  line `Directors of the said Association.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (68685)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Proprietors of shares to be members of Association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68685&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1 * * * Every proprietor of a share of`
  line `the said Capital Stock, who shall cease to be a proprietor of such Stock, shall cease to be a member of`
  line `the corporation created by this Act; and ^2* * * every person who shall become a proprietor of the said`
  line `Capital Stock, shall become a member of the corporation created by this Act; and shall, in respect of`
  line `his share or shares of the said Capital Stock, be under the same liabilities under which an original`
  line `proprietor of the said Capital Stock would be.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "And it is hereby enacted, that" omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word "that" omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (68686)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `First Directors of Association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68686&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * The business of the said Association shall be managed`
  line `by six Directors, and ^2* * * Francis Macnaghten, Joseph Walker, Jasper Ouseley, Richard Howe`
  line `Cockerell, Alexander Colvin, Joseph Willis, and James Church, Esquires, shall be the first Directors`
  line `of the said Association`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word “that” omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (68687)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Removal and election of Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68687&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * Every Director of the said Association may be`
  line `removed by a general meeting of the proprietors, and ^2* * * every future Director of the said`
  line `Association shall be elected by such a general meeting`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word “that” omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (68688)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Directors to go out by rotation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68688&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `1* * * A rotation among the Directors of the said`
  line `Association shall be settled by lot, so that two of the said Directors may go out of office on the`
  line `Monday following the 15th day of May, in every year, and 2* * * on the Monday following the`
  line `15th day of May, in every year, a general meeting of proprietors shall be held, at which two Directors`
  line `shall be chosen, and that no Director going out by such rotation shall be capable of being re-elected,`
  line `till the Monday after the 15th of May in the year next following.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (68689)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Election of successor, when Director ceases to be so otherwise than by rotation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68689&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1* * *`
  line `If any Director of the said Association shall cease to be a Director, otherwise than by the operation of`
  line `the rule of rotation aforesaid, the Directors of the said Association shall, with all convenient speed`
  line `after such public notice as is hereinafter directed, call an extraordinary general meeting of the`
  line `proprietors for the purpose of choosing a successor and such successor shall come into the same place`
  line `in the rotation aforesaid in which the Director whom he has succeeded was.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (68690)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title [Repealed].
  content `[Qualifications of Directors[.—[Repealed by Act 5 of 1854, Section 1].`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68690&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (68691)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Directors to be residents of Bengal Presidency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68691&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * No person shall be capable of being`
  line `a Director of the said Association, unless he be resident within the Territories subject to the`
  line `Presidency of Fort William in Bengal`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (68692)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title [Repealed].
  content `[Ordinary meetings.[--[Repealed by Act 5 of 1854, Section 1.]`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68692&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (68693)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Adjournment of ordinary meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68693&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * Any ordinary general meeting of the said`
  line `Association may adjourn itself to a future day, and may, on the day to which it shall have so`
  line `adjourned itself, resume its proceedings, and transact any business which it would have been`
  line `competent to transact on the day when it originally assembled.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (68694)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Extraordinary general meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68694&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * Extraordinary general meetings of the said`
  line `Association shall be held according to such rules as may be made for that purpose, in the Bye-laws of`
  line `the said Association; provided always, that no such extraordinary general meeting shall be held`
  line `without a previous notice of not less than fourteen days, which notice shall be published in not less`
  line `than two newspapers printed at Calcutta.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (68695)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Voting at general meetings Qualification for voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68695&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * At General Meetings of the Proprietors, every election`
  line `and question shall be decided by a majority of votes; and`
  line
  line `Qualifications for voting.---^2* * * no proprietor shall be allowed to vote unless he be possessed of two or more shares of the Capital Stock`
  line `of the said Association, which shares shall have been registered in his name not less than three`
  line `calendar months before.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word “that” omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (68696)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Number of votes to which proprietors entitled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68696&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * At such general meetings, no`
  line `proprietor shall have more than eight votes, and ^2* * * the proprietors shall vote according to the`
  line `following scale:---`
  line `2 Shares shall entitle to 1 vote.`
  line `4 2 votes.`
  line `6 3`
  line `10 4`
  line `20 6`
  line `35 7`
  line `50 8`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word “that” omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (68697)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Votes of joint proprietors shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68697&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * If more persons than one, being partners in trade,`
  line `shall be joint proprietors of two or more shares of the said Capital Stock, and shall agree to give a`
  line `joint vote or joint votes, such joint vote or joint votes, shall be received in all respects as the vote or`
  line `votes of a single proprietor would be received`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (68698)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Voting by proxy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68698&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * Every proprietor entitled to vote at any general meeting may give a`
  line `proxy in writing, general or special, limited or unlimited, and signed by himself or by his attorney`
  line `duly authorized thereunto, to any other proprietor; and ^2* * * the proprietor to whom the proxy is`
  line `given, may vote on behalf of the proprietor who had given the proxy, according to the terms of such`
  line proxy.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word “that” omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (68699)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Authority of Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68699&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * The Directors of the said Association shall have authority to`
  line `expend the money of the said Association for the purpose of purchasing and erecting warehouses, and`
  line `of warehousing and bonding goods therein, and to make and fulfil contracts for the said purpose, and`
  line `to appoint and remove such servants as may be necessary for the said purpose and generally to`
  line `manage all the concerns of the said Association, subject to such rules as may be laid down in the`
  line `Bye-laws of the said Association, and to keep the seal of the said Association, and to use the said seal`
  line `in the affairs of the said Association, provided always, that the said seal shall never be affixed to any`
  line `instrument except in the presence and by the consent of three Directors, who shall sign their names on`
  line `every such instrument in token of their presence and consent.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (68700)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Calls for share money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. The words "And it is hereby enacted, that" omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68700&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * The Directors of the said Association shall have authority to`
  line `call on the proprietors to pay such instalment or instalments as shall, together with the instalments`
  line `already paid, amount to a sum not exceeding 50 per cent. on each share; and ^1* * * no further call shall be`
  line `made, except in consequence of a vote of a general meeting of the proprietors, authorising such`
  line `further call; provided always that no proprietor shall be called upon to pay more in proportion to his`
  line `share in the Capital Stock than any other proprietor.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (68701)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Interest to run on each call. Application of dividend in satisfaction of unpaid calls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68701&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * If any proprietor shall not pay any instalment which he`
  line `is lawfully called upon to pay, in the manner described in the last section, on the day appointed for`
  line `such payment, the said Association shall have a claim against such proprietor for interest on the`
  line `deficient sum, after the rate of 10 per cent. per annum; and`
  line
  line `Application of dividend in satisfaction of unpaid calls.---^1* * * it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Directors of the said Association to apply, in satisfaction of such instalment and of such interest, any`
  line `dividend due to such proprietor, placing every dividend so applied to the credit of such proprietor with`
  line `the said Association`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "And it is hereby enacted, that" omitted by s. 2 and Sch. I, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. The word "that" omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (68802)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to refuse to register transfer by defaulting proprietor. Power to sell shares to satisfy calls, and issue fresh certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68802&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * It shall be lawful for`
  line `the Directors of the said Association to refuse to register the transfer of any share belonging to any`
  line `proprietor who shall not have paid such instalment and interest as aforesaid; and ^2* * * in case such`
  line `instalment and interest shall not be paid within two months after notice to pay the same has been`
  line `given by the said Directors to such proprietor, or to his attorney or attorneys duly authorised, it shall`
  line `be lawful for the said Directors to sell by public sale the share or shares of such proprietor, to such an`
  line `extent as may be sufficient to satisfy such instalment and interest, and to grant, upon such sale,`
  line
  line `Power to sell shares to satisfy calls, and issue fresh certificates.---a new certificate or new`
  line `certificates to the purchaser of such share or shares whereupon the former certificate or certificates for`
  line `such share or shares shall become void, and if there be any surplus after such instalment and interest`
  line `have been satisfied, such surplus shall be paid on demand to the proprietor of such share or shares,`
  line `and shall, till demand, be credited in the books of the said Association to such proprietor, but no`
  line `interest shall run thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "And it is hereby enacted, that" omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The word "that" omitted by ibid. s. 2 and Sch. I`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (68703)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Extension of Act 25 of 1836 to warehouses of Association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68703&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * All the provisions`
  line `of ^2Act 25 of 1836, of the Governor General of India in council, relating to private licensed`
  line `Warehouses, shall be applicable to all Warehouses wherein the said Association shall receive bonded`
  line Goods.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "And it is hereby enacted, that" omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1873 (12 of 1873).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (68704)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to give general security for payment of import and export duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68704&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * It shall`
  line `be lawful for the said Association to give general security, by bond, under the seal of the said`
  line `Association, for payment of the full duties of importation on Goods, lodged in any Warehouse of the`
  line `said Association, or for the due exportation of such Goods; and if the said Association shall give such`
  line `bond, no security shall be required from any other party to the same effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (68705)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Rates for warehousing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68705&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * The Directors of the said Association shall, from time to`
  line `time, fix the rates at which the said Association will Warehouse Goods and receive Goods at its`
  line `Wharfs, and ^2* * * a table of such rates shall be placed at every Warehouse and Wharf of the said`
  line Association
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch.I`
  line
  line `2. The word “that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (68706)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Certificates of deposit, transferable by endorsement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68706&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * As often as any Goods are`
  line `lodged in any Warehouse of the said Association, the Secretary of the said Association shall deliver a warrant signed by him as such Secretary, to the person lodging such Goods, which warrant shall be, as`
  line `nearly as possible, in the form set forth in Schedule II annexed to this Act, and such warrant shall be`
  line `transferable by indorsement, and shall entitle any person to whom it may have been so transferred by`
  line `endorsement, to receive the Goods specified in such warrant on the same terms on which the person`
  line `who originally lodged those Goods would have been entitled to receive the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (68707)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Suits against Association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68707&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * All suits brought against the said Association shall be`
  line `brought in the Supreme Court of Judicature at Fort William in Bengal and not elsewhere.`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (68708)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Joint Stock of Association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68708&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * All the Joint Stock of the said Association of what kind`
  line `or description soever, and all the Land, Warehouses, Messuages, Tenements, Hereditaments, Premises`
  line `and Property acquired therewith, of which the said Association shall become in any manner`
  line `possessed, entitled to, or interested in, shall be held and enjoyed by the Proprietors thereof, and their`
  line `successors respectively, as Personal Estate, or as in the nature of Chattel Interests, and not as, or in the`
  line `nature of, Real Estate`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (68709)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Individual members not to be liable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68709&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * In order to define the liability of Proprietors or`
  line `shares, and to save harmless themselves and their respective Heirs, Executors, Administrators,`
  line `Representatives and Assigns, no Proprietor, his Heirs, Executors, Administrators, Representatives or`
  line `Assigns, shall be personally liable to any person or persons whatsoever by reason of being a`
  line `Proprietor in any event, or for or on account of any acts, deeds, contracts or liabilities of the said`
  line `Association, or of the Directors or Secretary thereof respectively, or under or by virtue of any`
  line `judgment or decree in any action or suit, but ^2* * * the party or parties having any legal or equitable`
  line `demand or claim for or on the account last aforesaid, or having obtained such judgment or decree as`
  line `last aforesaid, shall and may only recover the amount of such demand, claim, judgment or decree`
  line `from and out of or to the whole extent of the paid up Capital, accumulated Funds, Lands, Messuages,`
  line `Tenements, Hereditaments and Premises whatsoever and wheresoever, which may at the time belong`
  line `to the said Association, or to which they may at the time be entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. The words “that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (68710)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title [Repealed].
  content `[Bye-laws].--[Repealed by Act 5 of 1854, Section 1].`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68710&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (68711)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Increase of Capital Stock.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68711&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * It shall be lawful for the said Association to increase its`
  line `Capital Stock; provided always that no such increase shall take place unless it be authorized by a vote`
  line `of two extraordinary general meetings of Proprietors specially convened for that purpose, of which`
  line `meetings the second shall be held not less than three calendar months after the first.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (68712)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Option to original proprietors to subscribe in first instance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68712&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * In the event of such`
  line `increase, the Proprietors of the original Stock shall not be bound to subscribe, but shall in the first`
  line `instance have the option of subscribing for the increased Capital Stock in proportion to the share`
  line `which each has of the original Capital Stock; and so much of the additional Capital Stock as shall not`
  line `be subscribed for by the said Proprietors of the original stock, within one year after the passing of the`
  line `final resolution for the increase, shall be open to the public, and be sold, for the benefit of the said`
  line `Association, by public sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (68713)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Provisions of Act to apply to additional Stock.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68713&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * All the rules laid down in this Act`
  line `respecting the original Capital Stock of the said Association, shall be applicable to any additional`
  line `Stock which may be subscribed in the manner hereinbefore described`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (68714)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `East India Company to have right of pre-emption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68714&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * If the said Association shall be`
  line `desirous to dispose of any premises purchased by the said Association from the East India Company, the said East India Company shall the right of pre-emption, and the price shall be fixed by two`
  line `appraisers, the one named on the part of the said East India Company, and the other by the Directors`
  line `of the said Association; and if the said appraisers shall not agree on a price, the price shall be fixed by`
  line `an umpire named by the said appraisers.`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (68715)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Dissolution of Association by order of the Governor General in Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68715&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `[Dissolution of Association by order of the Governor General in Council.]----[Repealed by Act`
  line `5 of 1854, Section 1.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (68716)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Dissolution of Association by resolution of proprietors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68716&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * The said Association may`
  line `at any time be dissolved by a resolution to that effect of two-thirds in number and value of the`
  line `proprietors qualified to vote at two successive extraordinary meetings specially called for the purpose`
  line `of taking into consideration the expediency of such dissolution; provided that not less than three`
  line `months shall have elapsed between the first and second of such two extraordinary meetings.`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (68717)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Division of property on dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073&sectionId=68717&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00093_183805_1662013952073
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * Whenever the dissolution of the said`
  line `Association shall be ordered either by the ^2[Central Government], or by a vote of the said Association,`
  line `the Directors of the said Association shall cause all the property of the said Association to be`
  line `converted into money, and shall divide whatever surplus may remain after satisfying the debts of the`
  line `said Association among the proprietors in proportion to the shares which the proprietors have in the`
  line `Capital Stock of the said Association; and after such distribution the said Association shall forthwith`
  line `be dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted, that” omitted by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for “Governor General of India in Council”.`
